Storyline:


     Rich playgirl Kit Jordan is in Acapulco vacationing with her current husband, Pete Jordan, formerly an American beach boy working the Acapulco shores for rich women when the body of one of Pete's beach boy buddys washes ashore. On his wrist is a bracelet engraved with "Love is thin ice." The police, of course, investigate whether it was murder or suicide and conflict arises when the dead man's old girlfriend, Carol, makes a play for Pete, and beach boy Hank tries to score with Kit, and the stability of the marriage is put to the test.
